Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED IS: 1. A computer- implemented method, comprising: providing, by a first computing device, an indication that the first computing device accepts user registration of user accounts over a wireless connection; after or in connection with providing the indication, receiving a request to initiate the user registration from a second computing device over the wireless connection; establishing an encrypted connection between the first computing device and the second computing device in response to the request; receiving, over the encrypted connection, an account token for obtaining user account information associated with a user account on the second computing device; obtaining, based on the account token, the user account information from a server; and registering the user account with the first computing device based on the obtained user account information in response to obtaining the user account information. 2. The computer-implemented method of claim 1 , further comprising: before receiving the request to initiate the user registration, automatically pairing the second computing device to the first computing device over the wireless connection. 3. The computer-implemented method of claim 2, wherein the wireless connection is a personal area network, and wherein the first computing device and second computing device communicate with each other over the personal area network using Bluetooth. 4. The computer-implemented method of claim 1 , wherein the account token is a universal credential token corresponding to the user account information. 5. The computer-implemented method of claim 1 , wherein receiving the request, establishing the encrypted connection, receiving the account token, obtaining the user account information, and registering the user account are performed without any physical interaction with the first computing device. 6. The computer-implemented method of claim 1 , further comprising: authorizing use of the first computing device in accordance with the user account information based on the second computing device being within a predetermined distance of the first computing device. 7. The computer- implemented method of claim 1 , further comprising: after registering the user account information, providing the second computing device an access key; placing the first computing device into a locked mode wherein access to the first computing device is restricted; receiving the access key from the second computing device; and removing the first computing device from the locked mode based on the access key from the second computing device. 8. The computer-implemented method of claim 7, further comprising: before removing the first computing device from the locked mode, validating the access key received from the second computing device based on a previously stored key associated with the second computing device at the first computing device. 9. The computer-implemented method of claim 7, further comprising: receiving a response code from the second computing device; automatically removing the first computing device from the locked mode if the response code indicates the second computing device is in an unlocked mode; and displaying a security access screen that includes an input for entering a passcode, and waiting for entry of the passcode before unlocking the first computing device, if the response code does not indicate the second computing device is in the unlocked mode. 10. The computer-implemented method of claim 1 , further comprising: after registering the user account information, identifying one or more account- linked devices associated with the account information; 

 receiving one or more selections corresponding to one or more of the account- linked devices; and in response to receiving the one or more selections, automatically providing pairing information and respective access keys to respective selected devices, the pairing information configured to enable a respective device to automatically pair with the first computing device, a respective access key configured to, when received by the first computing device, cause the first computing device to remove the first computing device from the locked mode. 1 1. The computer-implemented method of claim 1 , wherein the request to initiate the user registration corresponds to a predetermined code known to the first computing device. 12. A computer program product tangibly embodied in a computer-readable storage device and comprising instructions that, when executed by a first computing device, cause the computing device to: broadcast an ability to accept user registration of user accounts over a wireless connection; receive, after or in connection with the broadcasting, an initiation of the user registration from a second computing device over the wireless connection; receive, over the wireless connection, an account token associated with a user account; obtain, from a server, user account information for the user account based on the account token; and register the user account with the first computing device in response to obtaining the user account information. 13. The computer program product of claim 12, wherein the wireless connection is a personal area network, and wherein the computing device and mobile device communicate with each other over the personal area network using Bluetooth. 14. The computer program product of claim 12, wherein receiving the request, establishing the encrypted connection, receiving the account token, obtaining the user account information, and registering the user account information are performed without any physical interaction with the first computing device and the second computing device. 15. The computer program product of claim 12, wherein the instructions, when executed by the computing device, further causing the computing device to: after registering the user account, providing the second computing device an access key; enter into a locked mode wherein access to the first computing device is restricted; receive the access key from the second computing device while in the locked mode; and exit the locked mode based on the access key from the second computing device. 16. The computer program product of claim 15, wherein the instructions, when executed by the computing device, further causing the computing device to: before exiting the locked mode, validate the access key received from the second computing device based on a previously stored key associated with the second computing device at the first computing device. 17. The computer program product of claim 15, wherein the instructions, when executed by the computing device, further causing the computing device to: receive a response code from the second computing device; automatically exit the locked mode if the response code indicates the second computing device is in an unlocked mode; and display a security access screen that includes an input for entering a passcode, and waiting for entry of the passcode before exiting the locked mode, if the response code does not indicate the second computing device is in the unlocked mode. 18. The computer program product of claim 12, wherein the instructions, when executed by the computing device, further causing the computing device to: after registering the user account, identify one or more account-linked devices associated with the user account; receive one or more selections corresponding to one or more of the account- linked devices; in response to receiving the one or more selections, automatically provide pairing information and respective access keys to respective selected devices, the pairing information configured to enable a respective device to automatically pair with the first computing device; and on receiving the pairing information and one of the provided respective access keys from a respective device, automatically pair with the respective device and exit the locked mode. 19. The computer program product of claim 12, wherein the initiation of the user registration comprising receiving from the second computing device a predetermined code known to the first computing device. 20. A system, comprising: one or more processors; and a memory including instructions that, when executed by the one or more processors, cause the one or more processors to facilitate the steps of: indicating a first computing device accepts user registration of user accounts over a wireless connection; receiving, after or in connection with the broadcasting, an initiation of the user registration from a second computing device over the wireless connection; receiving, over the wireless connection, an encrypted account token associated with a user account; decrypting the account token; obtaining, from a server, user account information for the user account based on the decrypted account token; 

 registering the user account with the first computing device in response to obtaining the user account information; and automatically authorizing use of the computing device based on the user account.
